
Practice using keys when writing playbook in vim

Note: before using press ESC to go into ESC mode

1) :set cuc     (to turn on vertical line (cursor column)

2) :set nocuc   (to turn off cursor column)

3) Use Two Spaces wherever required to add space

4) for bigger playbook if you need to fold the lines

     zfG    (to fold lines)
     za     (to unfold lines)
